In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims March 1, 2013, as Read Across America Day. He emphasizes the importance of literacy and the transformative power of reading. The article also pays tribute to Theodor Seuss Geisel, better known as Dr. Seuss, whose works have inspired a passion for reading in many people. Obama calls upon children, families, educators, librarians, public officials, and all Americans to observe the day with appropriate programs and activities. The proclamation highlights the significance of books in shaping our lives and encourages everyone to empower the next generation with the tools they need for success.